<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Joe Hildebrand bid farewell to Studio 10 viewers last week after seven years as a panellist on the Channel 10 morning show.</p>

<p>And on Wednesday, the 44-year-old journalist discussed the real reason he quit the program in his column for New Corp.</p>

<p>Joe dispelled rumours he was 'forced out' by the network because he was 'too right-wing or too left-wing or too unpredictable'.</p>

<p>'I went out in a blaze of glory': Joe Hildebrand revealed the real reason he quit Studio 10 after seven years on the breakfast show</p>

<p>He said the reality of his departure was far more mundane.</p>

<p>'The boring truth is the network just needed to cut costs and I quit rather than take on a lesser role,' he explained.</p>

<p>'But nobody would want to watch that, so tell the world I went out in a blaze of glory,' he jokingly added. </p>

<p>Ahead of the rumours: The 44-year-old dispelled rumours he was 'forced out' by the network because he was 'too right-wing or too left-wing or too unpredictable'</p>

<p>The truth: He explained, 'The boring truth is the network just needed to cut costs and I quit rather than take on a lesser role'</p>

<p>Joe's column comes after Channel 10 aired a promo for Studio 10 on Monday night that featured him, despite the fact he's no longer on the panel.</p>

<p>He was shown in the promo alongside fellow panellist Kerri-Anne Kennerley and newsreader Natarsha Belling, who have also been sacked. </p>

<p>He tweeted a photo of the ad and wrote: 'Not sure they ran the right promo tonight! Best of luck though gang!' </p>

<p>'Not sure they ran the right promo tonight!' Joe's column comes after Channel Ten aired a promo for Studio 10 that featured him and fellow sacked stars Kerri-Anne Kennerley (right, in blue) and veteran newsreader Natarsha Belling (top centre, in orange) late on Monday night</p>

<p>On Thursday, Joe broke down in tears live on air as he revealed he had come to the difficult decision to leave after seven years. </p>

<p>'I am leaving Studio 10. I have given it a huge amount of thought. It's been really hard, but also really lovely to be able to look back on all the things we have done.</p>

<p>'We all know the show is getting a bit of a shake-up. Channel 10 and my lovely bosses asked me if I'd stay on in a new role. We talked about it openly and warmly about what that might look like.'</p>

<p>Speaking of his bosses' reaction when he told them he was leaving Studio 10, Joe said: 'They're really lovely about it, so don't lash out at them!'</p>

<p>'I have given it a huge amount of thought': On Thursday, Joe broke down in tears live on air as he revealed he had come to the difficult decision to leave after seven years. He said: '[I want to] give the show a chance to breathe and have a fresh start without me hanging around'</p>

<p>'I just thought, it's probably just better to draw a line under this amazing little story that I've been lucky enough to be a part of,' he added.</p>

<p>'[I want to] give the show a chance to breathe and have a fresh start without me hanging around.'</p>

<p>Taking over Joe's role as co-host alongside Sarah Harris is Dancing with the Stars judge Tristan MacManus, who began on Monday.</p>

<p>New look Studio 10: Taking over Joe's role as co-host is Dancing With The Stars judge Tristan MacManus, who began on Monday. Pictured left is Sarah with Tristan </p>
